  "id": 157,
  "Title": "Mississippi Corn Pudding",
  "Ingredients": "['5 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted and cooled slightly, plus more for greasing', '2 large eggs, beaten', '⅓ cup sugar', '½ cup whole milk', '¼ cup heavy cream', '¾ cup sour cream', '½ cup all-purpose flour', '½ cup coarse yellow cornmeal', '1 teaspoon kosher salt', '⅛ teaspoon white pepper', '⅛ teaspoon paprika', '⅛ teaspoon baking soda', '¼ cup chopped yellow onion', '½ cup chopped celery', '1 pound fresh corn kernels, cut from 4 cobs', '1 cup shredded cheddar cheese', '1 cup butter cracker crumbs, such as Ritz']",
  "Instructions": "Set a rack in the lower third of the oven. Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a 9 by 13-inch casserole dish with butter, making sure to get in all the corners and sides of the dish.\r\nIn a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs and sugar until well combined. Add the melted butter, milk, heavy cream, and sour cream and whisk to incorporate.\r\nIn a large bowl, whisk together the flour, cornmeal, salt, pepper, paprika, and baking soda.\r\nUsing a spatula, fold the wet ingredients, 1 cup at a time, into the dry ingredients until well combined.\r\nFold in the onion, celery, corn, and cheese.\r\nPour the batter into the prepared baking dish and sprinkle the cracker crumbs on top. Bake the pudding for 30 to 40 minutes, rotating halfway through, until lightly browned on top and the tip of a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.",
  "Image_Name": "mississippi-corn-pudding",
  "Cleaned_Ingredients": "['5 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted and cooled slightly, plus more for greasing', '2 large eggs, beaten', '⅓ cup sugar', '½ cup whole milk', '¼ cup heavy cream', '¾ cup sour cream', '½ cup all-purpose flour', '½ cup coarse yellow cornmeal', '1 teaspoon kosher salt', '⅛ teaspoon white pepper', '⅛ teaspoon paprika', '⅛ teaspoon baking soda', '¼ cup chopped yellow onion', '½ cup chopped celery', '1 pound fresh corn kernels, cut from 4 cobs', '1 cup shredded cheddar cheese', '1 cup butter cracker crumbs', 'such as Ritz']"
