  "id": 197,
  "Title": "Agua de Limón con Chía (Limeade With Chia Seeds)",
  "Ingredients": "['3 large limes, quartered', '4 cups water', '1/2 cup sugar, or more if needed', '1/4 cup chia seeds']",
  "Instructions": "Put the limes, water, and sugar in a blender and pulse 3 to 4 times, just enough to extract the juice from the limes but not crush the skins (which would make the drink too bitter). Strain through a fi ne-mesh sieve into a pitcher. Taste and add more sugar if you like.\r\nWhisk in the chia seeds and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, until completely chilled. Stir before serving, then serve over ice.",
  "Image_Name": "agua-de-limon-con-chia-limeade-with-chia-seeds",
  "Cleaned_Ingredients": "['3 large limes, quartered', '4 cups water', '1/2 cup sugar, or more if needed', '1/4 cup chia seeds']"
