  "id": 198,
  "Title": "Lágrimas de la Virgen (Beet Cooler With Fruits)",
  "Ingredients": "['4 red beets', '8 cups water', '1 cup sugar', '1 small apple (Fuji or McIntosh), peeled and diced', '1 banana, diced', '1 small orange, peeled and diced', '4 leaves romaine lettuce, cut into thin strips', 'Juice of 1 lime']",
  "Instructions": "Peel the beets. Cut them into chunks and pass them through a juicer.\r\nCombine the water and sugar in a pitcher and stir until the sugar has dissolved. Add the beet juice.\r\nRefrigerate until completely chilled. Add the apple, banana, orange, and lettuce, then stir in the lime juice (which will help prevent the fruit from browning). Serve chilled over ice, if desired.\r\nAlternately, divide the mixed diced fruit among the glasses; place the beet water in a pitcher for guests to pour over.",
  "Image_Name": "lagrimas-de-la-virgen-beet-cooler-fany-gerson",
  "Cleaned_Ingredients": "['4 red beets', '8 cups water', '1 cup sugar', '1 small apple (Fuji or McIntosh), peeled and diced', '1 banana, diced', '1 small orange, peeled and diced', '4 leaves romaine lettuce, cut into thin strips', 'Juice of 1 lime']"
