  "Title": "Sweet Pickle Potato Salad",
  "Ingredients": "['1 pound small red potatoes, scrubbed', 'Salt and pepper', '½ cup finely chopped onion', '½ cup sweet pickle relish', '½ cup mayonnaise', '4 hard-boiled eggs, finely chopped']",
  "Instructions": "Put the potatoes in a large pot and add enough cold water to cover them by 1 inch. Add a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil and cook until the potatoes are tender but not mushy, about 15 minutes. Drain. Set aside until cool enough to handle.\r\nWhile the potatoes are still warm, cut them into quarters and place them in a large bowl. Add the onion, relish, mayonnaise, and eggs. Toss until well combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper.\r\nCover and chill until ready to serve, at least 1 hour or up to overnight.",
